br.com.caelum.vraptor

Annotation Type BeforeCall


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=METHOD)
public @interface BeforeCall
    Executes a method before the current call, and you can't have more than one method annotated with BeforeCall in the same class. The target method must have no parameters. The method br.com.caelum.vraptor.interceptor.SimpleInterceptorStack#next will call implicity after the execution. \@BeforeCall public void intercept() { System.out.println("code executed before stack"); }
